      • toRowValue

        public static Object toRowValue(Object item,
                                DataType type)

        Converts a Java object (simple or compound, e.g. Maps and Arrays) or Row object (for Arrays, Maps, and StructType) into a Row compatible value or values. In the latter case for Maps, the incoming Row must have an associated schema and results in a MapType.

        NOTE: If there is a conversion error with a complex type (Map, Array, StructType), the function will set the returned value for the sub-element to 'null' if the DataType allows it, i.e. ArrayType.containsNull().

        NOTE: Does not handle the following DataTypes:

        • UserDefinedType
        • CalendarIntervalType

        Details for accepted conversion values.

        BinaryType
        • ByteBuffer
        • byte[]
        BooleanType
        • Boolean
        • Case-insensitive String value of true or false
        DateType
        • Long value of milliseconds since epoch
        • String value of milliseconds since epoch
        • Date value
        • DateTime value
        • or the following String value:
             datetime          = time | date-opt-time
   time              = 'T' time-element [offset]
   date-opt-time     = date-element ['T' [time-element] [offset]]
   date-element      = std-date-element | ord-date-element | week-date-element
   std-date-element  = yyyy ['-' MM ['-' dd]]
   ord-date-element  = yyyy ['-' DDD]
   week-date-element = xxxx '-W' ww ['-' e]
   time-element      = HH [minute-element] | [fraction]
   minute-element    = ':' mm [second-element] | [fraction]
   second-element    = ':' ss [fraction]
   fraction          = ('.' | ',') digit+
   offset            = 'Z' | (('+' | '-') HH [':' mm [':' ss [('.' | ',') SSS]]])
        TimestampType
        • Long value of milliseconds since epoch
        • String value of milliseconds since epoch
        • Date value
        • DateTime value
        • or the following String value:
             datetime          = time | date-opt-time
   time              = 'T' time-element [offset]
   date-opt-time     = date-element ['T' [time-element] [offset]]
   date-element      = std-date-element | ord-date-element | week-date-element
   std-date-element  = yyyy ['-' MM ['-' dd]]
   ord-date-element  = yyyy ['-' DDD]
   week-date-element = xxxx '-W' ww ['-' e]
   time-element      = HH [minute-element] | [fraction]
   minute-element    = ':' mm [second-element] | [fraction]
   second-element    = ':' ss [fraction]
   fraction          = ('.' | ',') digit+
   offset            = 'Z' | (('+' | '-') HH [':' mm [':' ss [('.' | ',') SSS]]])

        Note: The precision is limited to milliseconds; nanosecond resolution is not supported.

        DoubleType
        • Double
        • Number
        • String value of a Double
        FloatType
        • Float
        • Number
        • String value of a Float
        IntegerType
        • Integer
        • Number
        • String value of an Integer
        LongType
        • Long
        • Number
        • String value of a Long
        NullType
        • null
        ByteType
        • Byte
        • Number
        • String value of a Byte
        ShortType
        • Short
        • Number
        • String value of a Short
        DecimalType
        • Long
        • Double
        • String value of a BigDecimal
        • BigInteger
        • BigDecimal

        Note: For Double and String conversions, the parsed value will be rounded down, per RoundingMode.HALF_DOWN convention.

        StringType
        • String
        ArrayType
        • List of supported DataTypes
        • Row of supported DataTypes
        MapType
        • Map with key/value pairs of supported DataTypes
        • Row of supported DataTypes. NOTE: The Row must have an associated schema or conversion will fail.
        StructType
        • Map with the following restrictions: keys must be Strings and match the names of the fields in the StructType, values must be supported DataTypes.
        • List of supported DataTypes; list must have an exact count and in-order list of values for the StructType
        • Row of supported DataTypes; Row must have an exact count and in-order list of values for the StructType
        Parameters:
        item - The value for conversion
        type - The DataType of the field
        Returns:
        A Row-compatible value
        See Also:
        Spark SQL Data Types
